Find her!

269
00:47:10,695 --> 00:47:12,663
Don't look in the eyes!

270
00:47:24,008 --> 00:47:25,032
Five!

271
00:47:48,199 --> 00:47:49,962
Seven!
Nine!

272
00:47:58,543 --> 00:47:59,908
No!

273
00:48:12,724 --> 00:48:13,986
We have to go after them!

274
00:48:14,058 --> 00:48:17,789
What? 8? Where's...
Where's 8?

275
00:48:17,862 --> 00:48:21,662
That thing has them! It's taking them
back to the Machine!

276
00:48:22,500 --> 00:48:24,263
Then it's too late.

277
00:48:24,802 --> 00:48:26,793
We... We have to
get out of here.

278
00:48:26,938 --> 00:48:28,929
We must try to find
another safe place.

279
00:48:29,007 --> 00:48:32,875
No more hiding. We're going
after them! All of us.

280
00:48:34,278 --> 00:48:38,305
Need I remind you of the outcome
of your last heroic venture?

281
00:48:52,263 --> 00:48:54,697
I can't let this
happen to them.

282
00:50:19,851 --> 00:50:21,375
I'm going in.

283
00:50:21,953 --> 00:50:23,318
I'm coming with you.

284
00:50:23,387 --> 00:50:26,083
No. I need you here.

285
00:50:27,592 --> 00:50:31,494
If I don't make it back,
destroy it.

286
00:50:37,101 --> 00:50:39,296
Wait! How?

287
00:50:50,915 --> 00:50:56,012
So then, let's hear it.
What's your brilliant scheme?

288
00:50:58,256 --> 00:50:59,951
We’ll need a full barrel.

289
00:52:07,758 --> 00:52:10,318
Hey! Over here!

290
00:52:58,409 --> 00:52:59,876
Where are they?

291
00:52:59,944 --> 00:53:03,311
It's been too long.
We have to do it now.

292
00:53:03,381 --> 00:53:05,440
No! They need more time.

293
00:53:10,521 --> 00:53:12,421
Help me pull it down!

294
00:53:41,886 --> 00:53:43,911
They're coming!
They're coming!

295
00:53:43,988 --> 00:53:46,479
Help! Help!

296
00:53:49,160 --> 00:53:51,458
No! Not yet!

297
00:53:52,630 --> 00:53:54,621
Let go, you fool!

298
00:53:55,066 --> 00:53:56,260
Five!

299
00:53:57,168 --> 00:53:58,726
We're coming!

300
00:53:59,103 --> 00:54:00,365
Now!

301
00:55:24,855 --> 00:55:26,447
Good riddance.

302
00:55:27,958 --> 00:55:29,357
It's done.

303
00:56:13,838 --> 00:56:15,396
Sound.

304
00:56:17,675 --> 00:56:20,576
Sound.

305
00:56:22,580 --> 00:56:24,172
Sound.

306
00:56:24,248 --> 00:56:25,579
Thank you.

307
00:56:44,368 --> 00:56:45,494
Hmm.

308
00:57:29,813 --> 00:57:34,682
The Machine!
Everybody, the Machine!

309
00:57:34,752 --> 00:57:36,083
Run away!

310
00:57:40,758 --> 00:57:42,453
No! No!

311
00:57:44,395 --> 00:57:46,329
There's nothing we can do!

312
00:57:55,306 --> 00:57:57,365
No! No! No!

313
00:57:58,442 --> 00:57:59,704
No!

314
00:58:10,621 --> 00:58:13,146
They... They've
been trapped!

315
00:58:17,227 --> 00:58:18,785
To the bridge!

316
00:58:27,771 --> 00:58:30,934
No! They're trapped!
They're trapped inside!

317
00:58:31,008 --> 00:58:32,703
Six, come on!

318
00:58:32,776 --> 00:58:34,641
Get off the bridge!

319
00:58:52,896 --> 00:58:55,888
No! Stop!
You mustn't destroy it!

320
00:58:55,966 --> 00:58:56,990
Get away, Six!

321
00:58:57,067 --> 00:58:59,365
You mustn't destroy it!
Don't destroy it!

322
00:58:59,436 --> 00:59:00,733
They're trapped!
They're trapped!

323
00:59:00,804 --> 00:59:03,034
They're inside!
They're inside!

324
00:59:16,887 --> 00:59:18,218
Run!

325
00:59:20,324 --> 00:59:21,484
Jump!

326
00:59:23,694 --> 00:59:29,633
Go back to the first room!
He'll show you the source.

327
00:59:50,087 --> 00:59:51,281
It must be destroyed.

328
00:59:51,355 --> 00:59:54,756
No. No, we can't!
Didn't you hear him?

329
00:59:54,825 --> 00:59:58,056
They're trapped inside.
We can still save them.

330
00:59:58,128 --> 00:59:59,925
What? How?

331
00:59:59,997 --> 01:00:03,228
We have to find the source.
It holds the answer.

332
01:00:05,502 --> 01:00:06,799
We need to destroy it.

333
01:00:06,870 --> 01:00:09,065
But there's still a chance!

334
01:00:13,010 --> 01:00:14,739
We're out of time.

335
01:00:16,447 --> 01:00:18,813
Nine, they're gone.

336
01:00:21,251 --> 01:00:22,718
You're wrong.

337
01:00:24,021 --> 01:00:25,318
Nine...

338
01:00:26,223 --> 01:00:27,656
Let him go.

339
01:01:31,522 --> 01:01:33,387
<i>Greetings, Nine.</i>

340
01:01:34,158 --> 01:01:37,787
<i>It had such promise,
my Great Machine.</i>

341
01:01:38,328 --> 01:01:41,354
<i>It was meant to be
an instrument of progress,</i>

342
01:01:42,366 --> 01:01:43,799
<i>of creation.</i>

343
01:01:44,768 --> 01:01:48,727
<i>That was the agreement
our Chancellor failed to honor.</i>

344
01:01:50,207 --> 01:01:53,643
<i>Though the fault is
hardly his alone to bear.</i>

345
01:01:54,678 --> 01:01:58,478
<i>The Machine was born
purely of my intellect,</i>

346
01:01:59,683 --> 01:02:03,449
<i>which I now know
was not enough.</i>

347
01:02:05,055 --> 01:02:10,152
<i>My creation was hopelessly flawed
and indeed dangerous,</i>

348
01:02:10,227 --> 01:02:13,458
<i>for it lacked the human soul</i>

349
01:02:13,530 --> 01:02:17,933
<i>and could be easily corrupted
by those who controlled it.</i>

350
01:02:18,001 --> 01:02:21,562
<i>That is why I'm
making each of you.</i>

351
01:02:21,638 --> 01:02:24,334
<i>You are all that's
left of humanity.</i>

352
01:02:25,209 --> 01:02:29,578
<i>You are all
the pieces of my soul.</i>

353
01:02:32,049 --> 01:02:36,850
<i>Together, you and this device
shall protect the future.</i>

354
01:02:38,322 --> 01:02:42,986
<i>Look closely and
remember what you see.</i>

355
01:04:14,051 --> 01:04:15,211
Fire!

356
01:04:27,097 --> 01:04:29,429
Quickly!
<i>I now know the truth!</i>

357
01:04:30,801 --> 01:04:32,428
The Scientist!

358
01:04:33,270 --> 01:04:35,932
It's the Scientist.
He's the source!

359
01:04:36,974 --> 01:04:38,839
He gave us his soul.

360
01:04:39,843 --> 01:04:41,310
We are him.

361
01:04:47,718 --> 01:04:49,242
Load the cannon!

362
01:04:49,319 --> 01:04:51,947
Stop! You’ll destroy
the talisman!

363
01:04:54,358 --> 01:04:55,620
It's too late!

364
01:05:32,896 --> 01:05:34,830
Quick. Quick, get in.

365
01:05:38,402 --> 01:05:40,529
We need to take the talisman
from the Machine.

366
01:05:40,604 --> 01:05:42,231
It can be used against it.

367
01:05:42,305 --> 01:05:44,535
I'll lure it to me,
and then you'll have a chance.

368
01:05:44,608 --> 01:05:48,044
No. Nine, don't do this.
What if you're wrong?

369
01:05:48,111 --> 01:05:51,103
I'll show you how to use it.
It'll be okay.

370
01:05:54,785 --> 01:05:56,150
This is the sequence.

371
01:06:33,557 --> 01:06:34,649
No!

372
01:06:35,625 --> 01:06:38,890
Please, we can't
do this with out you.

373
01:06:40,397 --> 01:06:42,558
They all died
because of me.

374
01:06:42,866 --> 01:06:45,733
I started this and
now I need to finish it.

375
01:06:49,406 --> 01:06:52,500
<i>They left us nothing.
Nothing.</i>

376
01:06:53,710 --> 01:06:56,474
<i>Why do we have to
right their wrongs?</i>

377
01:06:57,214 --> 01:07:00,843
<i>Sometimes,
one must be sacrificed.</i>

378
01:07:03,920 --> 01:07:05,080
No!

379
01:08:14,257 --> 01:08:15,724
You did it!

380
01:08:18,228 --> 01:08:20,321
No, I didn't.

381
01:08:23,233 --> 01:08:24,530
Not yet.

382
01:11:19,642 --> 01:11:21,371
They're free now.

383
01:11:52,642 --> 01:11:54,371
<i>What happens next?</i>

384
01:11:55,111 --> 01:11:57,102
<i>I'm not sure, exactly.</i>

385
01:11:57,947 --> 01:12:00,142
<i>But this world is ours now.</i>

386
01:12:01,918 --> 01:12:04,011
<i>It's what we make of it.</i>
